#!/usr/bin/env python3
"""Phase 3 extension: Grade 11, Days 71-80 (fifth Grade 11 batch, taking
the grade from 70 to 80 days). Topics chosen to avoid any overlap with the
existing Day 1-70 set (see data/grade11.json / data/grade11.ts): absurdist
fiction and the Theatre of the Absurd, the dramatic monologue, data
visualization and statistical rhetoric, literary journalism and creative
non-fiction, the anecdote in oral storytelling, the semicolon/colon and
sentence-combining, historical fiction and the ethics of fictionalizing
the past, the definition essay, paratext and the epigraph; ellipses and
hyperbolas, matrices, the pigeonhole principle, direct/indirect proof and
proof by contradiction, sinusoidal modelling of periodic phenomena,
box-and-whisker plots and outliers, point discontinuities in rational
functions, the number e, mortgages and amortization; enzyme structure and
inhibition, DNA replication/transcription/translation, taxonomy and the
three-domain system, keystone species and trophic cascades, blood glucose
regulation and diabetes, marine ecosystems and ocean zonation, the stress
response and the HPA axis, mutations, ecological succession; hydrates and
water of crystallization, the ideal gas law, aromatic compounds, nuclear
fission and fusion, weak acid/base equilibria (Ka/Kb), the activity series
of metals, the solubility product constant (Ksp), combustion reactions,
ocean acidification.

Topics were checked closely against near-neighbours already on the books
to avoid overlap: "The Dramatic Monologue" is a distinct poetic form from
Day 67's confessional poem and Day 68's elegy; "Historical Fiction" is
distinct from Day 77 (this batch) being new and from Day 13's global
literature and Day 46's war literature/testimony; "Data Visualization and
Statistical Rhetoric" is distinct from Day 63's general news bias and
fact-checking lesson and Day 55's algorithmic bias lesson; "Ellipses and
Hyperbolas" extends Day 69's circles into the rest of the conic-section
family; "Direct, Indirect, and Proof by Contradiction" is a distinct proof
technique from Day 55's mathematical induction; "Box-and-Whisker Plots and
Outlier Detection" is distinct from Day 64's central tendency/spread, Day
37's standard deviation, and Day 43's normal distribution; "Enzyme
Structure, Function, and Inhibition" and "DNA Replication, Transcription,
and Translation" fill a genuine gap -- no prior day names either the core
biochemistry-of-enzymes or the central-dogma topic directly, distinct from
Day 36's gene expression/regulation and Day 66's bioinformatics; "Blood
Glucose Regulation and Diabetes" narrows in on a single hormonal system
the way Day 54's "Vision and the Eye" narrowed in from the general
nervous/endocrine survey on Day 10; "Marine Ecosystems and Ocean
Zonation" is distinct from Day 33's biomes/global-ecosystems survey and
Day 69's freshwater ecosystems/watershed lesson; "Ecological Succession"
and "Keystone Species and Trophic Cascades" are distinct ecological
processes not covered by Day 9's population dynamics, Day 41's nutrient
cycles, or Day 49's invasive species; "The Activity Series of Metals" and
"Solubility Product Constant (Ksp)" are distinct quantitative/predictive
tools from Day 46's solubility rules/precipitation and Day 43's general
equilibrium-constant lesson; "Aromatic Compounds and Benzene Derivatives"
and "Combustion Reactions and Fuel Chemistry" are distinct organic topics
from Day 7's general organic naming/reactions, Day 17's polymers, Day 21's
functional groups, Day 35's isomers, Day 44's esters/amides, and Day 55's
amines; "Ocean Acidification and Carbon Chemistry" is distinct from Day
64's acid rain/atmospheric chemistry (a different environmental pathway)
and pairs with, but does not duplicate, this batch's own Biology "Marine
Ecosystems" day. "Buffer Solutions" and "Catalysts and Reaction
Mechanisms" were again considered and rejected as too close to existing
Days 26 and 16/33/48 respectively, per the note already carried forward
from gen_grade11_days51_60.py and gen_grade11_days61_70.py.

Subject keys for Grade 11 are "English", "Functions", "Biology",
"Chemistry" (same as prior Grade 11 batches).

videoUrl is intentionally left unset for every subject --
fetch_video_ids.py fills these in automatically on its next daily run.
No embedded ASCII double-quote or apostrophe characters are used
anywhere in question/summary/option text; quotation marks and
apostrophes use the curly Unicode form (' " ").
"""
import sys
sys.path.insert(0, '/sessions/happy-laughing-ritchie/mnt/gradesbooster')
from gen_curriculum import sub, day, append_to

E11 = 'https://tvolearn.com/pages/grade-11-english'
F11 = 'https://tvolearn.com/pages/grade-11-functions'
B11 = 'https://tvolearn.com/pages/grade-11-biology'
C11 = 'https://tvolearn.com/pages/grade-11-chemistry'
RE, RF, RB, RC = (
    'TVO Learn: Grade 11 English',
    'TVO Learn: Grade 11 Functions',
    'TVO Learn: Grade 11 Biology',
    'TVO Learn: Grade 11 Chemistry',
)


def E(t, s, q):
    return sub('English', t, s, RE, E11, q)


def F(t, s, q):
    return sub('Functions', t, s, RF, F11, q)


def B(t, s, q):
    return sub('Biology', t, s, RB, B11, q)


def C(t, s, q):
    return sub('Chemistry', t, s, RC, C11, q)


